\key[strength]{Strength} allows you to hit harder. Add the bonus to
your to-hit rolls and to your damage rolls when using \textit{melee
  weapons}.

\key[dexterity]{Dexterity} allows you to aim better and to better
avoid attacks. Add the bonus to your to-hit roll when using
\textit{ranged weapons} (but not to your damage rolls) and subtract
the bonus from your \textit{armor class} (lower is better).

\key[constitution]{Constitution} determines your health. Add the bonus
to every \textit{hit die} (but never reduce a hit die below 1).

\key[intelligence]{Intelligence} determines your education. If you
have a positive bonus, it indicates how many \textit{extra languages}
you speak.

\key[wisdom]{Wisdom} determines how much in tune with the world you
are. Add the bonus to your \textit{saving throws against magic}
(spells, wands and the like).

\key[charisma]{Charisma} determines how well others react to you and
how many trustworthy people you can hire.

\newthought{Choose your \index{class}class}.

\hyperref[sec:fighter]{Fighter}: you can fight well; you will be able
to use magic swords; this is the simplest character to play
\marginnote[-2em]{\emph{What slaughter haunts your dreams? Whom do you
    hope to meet again in hell?}}

\hyperref[sec:magicuser]{Magic User}: you can memorize the spells in
your spell book but you cannot fight very well; you may be weak at
first but if you survive, you will be very powerful
\marginnote[-2em]{\emph{Who or what taught you sorcery? Why does it
    damn you?}}

\hyperref[sec:thief]{Thief}: You \hyperref[sec:skills]{skills} will
improve with time; surprise your enemies and deal double damage
\marginnote[-2em]{\emph{What do you love about adventure? Who taught
    you your tricks?}}

\hyperref[sec:cleric]{Cleric}: you can fight (but not as well as a
fighter) and you can work miracles granted to you by the gods (but
your spells are not as powerful as a wizard’s spells)
\marginnote[-3em]{\emph{What heresy infuriates you the most? When did
    you first hear the divine messengers?}}

\hyperref[sec:elf]{Elf}: you can memorize the spells in your spell
book and you can fight well but you will advance very slowly; you can
see in the dark; elves can live for ever; you need a minimum
intelligence of 9 \marginnote[-2em]{\emph{What do you love and hate
    about humans? What inhuman thing will you do or refrain from
    doing, again and again?}}

\hyperref[sec:dwarf]{Dwarf}: you are small but hardy and you can fight
well; you sometimes know things about underground constructions; you
can see in the dark; dwarves are hardy; you need a minimum
constitution of 9 \marginnote[-3em]{\emph{What feud curses your
    family? How come your parents wanted a child?}}

\hyperref[sec:halfling]{Halfling}: you are even smaller and you are
always barefoot; you can hide well and you are good at throwing and
shooting things; you are harder to hit by giants; halflings are
nimble; you need a minimum dexterity of 9 \marginnote[-4em]{\emph{Why
    did your parents let you? What consoles you for the lack of home
    and family?}}

